  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bc7 \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b9f \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel for essential services only - Special Notice",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government has decided to provide fuel only for essential services from midnight today (27) to July 10.",
        "According to Transport Minister Bandula Gunawardena, fuel will be distributed to a limited number of sectors, including ports, health, defense, electricity and the export industry.",
        "Cabinet Spokesperson, Transport Minister Bandula Gunawardena further stated that the issue of fuel shortage in the country was discussed in detail at the Cabinet meeting held today (27) and it was decided to provide fuel only for the current essential services.",
        "It is noteworthy that fuel for essential services should be distributed only at petrol stations of the Sri Lanka Transport Board and the 3rd Battalion."
      ],
